com.storytron.enginecommon

Interface StorytellerRemote

  • All Superinterfaces:
    java.rmi.Remote
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SwatRemote
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    Janus

    public interface StorytellerRemote
extends java.rmi.Remote
    This is the server interface. It provides services for running a story and navigating the log data generated by it.

    Before using the services, each client must create a session which is referenced by the client with a session identifier string (login(int, String, String), startStorytellerSession(int, String, String)). One user can have only one session at a time. So, creating a new session will destroy the previous one if any.

    If the session is created with the login(int, String, String) method a storyworld must be specified later with loadDeiktoFromZip(String, byte[]).

    Once there is a storyworld specified for a session, a story can be initiated with startStory(String, String, int[], byte[], boolean).

    Further communication can proceed then by using setResult(String, int) to indicate player selections and getTrigger(String) to obtain feedback about what's happening in the simulation.

    The exact order in which the calls must be made is dictated mainly by the Engine implementation. Currently getTrigger(String) must be called until getting all of the available data (StorytellerReturnData.inputEnded() returns true). Then setResult(String, int) must be called and the whole interaction must be repeated again.

    When a story is started, after each interaction with the server there may be log data to download. Log data may be buffered up to certain capacity, and then, subsequent calls to setResult(String, int) or getTrigger(String) may block to prevent generation of more log data. So it is necessary to download every now and then the log data with getLogData(String).

    The log data is a big tree collected in stages. While playing the story, only the closer levels to the root are collected. This is the data obtained with getLogData(String).

    While playing a story, complete log data branches can be obtained by requesting them with requestLogData(String, int, int, int). This will instruct the server to collect the data in that branch and make it available to download with getRequestedLogData(String). It is possible that a call to getRequestedLogData(String) does not return all of the requested data, but just the data that was collected at the time the call was made. It is also possible that the log data buffer is full, and the collector is blocked to wait for the buffer to be emptied. In those situations more calls to getRequestedLogData(String) will be needed to have all the requested data. It is the responsibility of the client to keep track of which requested data remains to be downloaded.

    Sessions will timeout after a while of inactivity from the part of the client. So some methods my throw a SessionLogoutException if called after the timeout.

    Clients are kindly requested to logout (logout(String)) when detecting that they will no longer use a session.

    While playing a session it is possible to obtained background information about the storyworld by using the methods #getPeople(String), #getPlaces(String) and #getThings(String). And the story book can be retrieved with getStorybookEntries(String).

    At any time the client can retrieve the engine state (getWorldState(String)). The engine state can be used later to resume the story with startStory(String, String, int[], byte[], boolean).

        Starts a story for the given username and storyworld.

        a vector containing
        • sessionID,

                                     throws java.rmi.RemoteException
        Called to get the topmost levels of the log tree that have been collected so far. The returned boolean is true iff the last tree is not complete, in such case it will be returned again in a future call to getLogData(String).
        Throws:

      • requestLogData

        boolean requestLogData(java.lang.String sessionID,
                       int fromTree,
                       int toTree,
                       int skipCommands)
                throws java.rmi.RemoteException,
                       SessionLogoutException
        Requests the engine to collect the branches starting at child fromTree and ending at child toTree (inclusive) of the root node.
        Returns:
        false if the request is not accepted. Can happen if too many requests are queued, or if fromTree>=toTree or if fromTree<0.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException
        SessionLogoutException

      • getRequestedLogData

        Triplet<java.lang.Integer,java.lang.Integer,Compressed<java.lang.Object[]>[]> getRequestedLogData(java.lang.String sessionID)
                                                                                           throws java.rmi.RemoteException,
                                                                                                  SessionLogoutException
        Gets data collected by the engine. The first Integer returned value is the index of the first returned tree. The second Integer returned value is -1 if the sent trees matches the requested, or is the index of the last delivered requested tree (likely to be partial). In case that this value is not -1, the client must expect more data to come from the server to complete the request.
        Returns:
        null if the data has not been requested, yet.
        Throws:
        java.rmi.RemoteException
        SessionLogoutException
